.SH "NAME"
lcb_connect \- Initiate connect sequence
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
cc [ flag \&... ] file\&... \-lcouchbase [ library \&... ]
.sp
.nf
#include <libcouchbase/couchbase\&.h>
.fi
.sp
.nf
lcb_error_t lcb_connect(lcb_t *instance);
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
Before libcouchbase may be used it must establish a connection to the Couchbase cluster to fetch the topology of the cluster\&. lcb_connect() initates the connect sequence, and the configuration callback specified with lcb_set_configuration_callback(3) is called when the topology is retrieved (or the error callback is called if an error occurs such as an incorrect host name etc)\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
.sp
lcb_connect() returns the LCB_SUCCESS on success, or a specific error code upon failure\&. See lcb_strerror(3) for more information\&.
